# 📄 README — OscillatorController & Incident

---

## 🔎 1. Description

This README contains:

- the modifications applied to the OscillatorController  
- the real deployment procedure  
- the incident description  

---

## ⚙️ 2. Modifications

The modifications are organized according to the blocks of the OscillatorController.cpp file:

1. CREATION OF CONTROLLER  
2. INITIALIZATION  
3. ADVANCE LOOP  
4. APPLY COMMAND  
5. OSCILLATION  
6. DEFAULT  
7. MOTION CONTROL MANAGER  
8. AUXILIARY METHODS  

---

### 2.1 — CREATION OF CONTROLLER

Removal of checks: StateStatusCheck & BaseStateCheck  

Removed code:

getInitialStateChecker().addStateCheck("stateStatus", ...);  
getStateChecker().addStateCheck("baseState", ...);  

Reason:

The controller was not starting when the robot is suspended.  
Oscillations are launched in this configuration.

---

### 2.2 — INITIALIZATION

Additions: gotoDefaultStartPos_  & gotoDefaultTargetPos_  

Allows defining a starting pose before oscillation.

CSV logging added with:

- time t  
- dt  
- chirp  
- measured positions  
- desired positions  

---

### 2.3 — ADVANCE LOOP

- CSV writing inside the loop  
- reset handling  
- first iteration initialization + GoToDefault  

---

### 2.4 — APPLY COMMAND

setJointsCommand(dt)

Choice between:

- default  
- sinus  
- chirp  

---

### 2.5 — OSCILLATION

Sinus: JointsOscillation()  
Chirp: calculateOscillationPACE()  0.1 → 2 Hz over 20 s  

---

### 2.6 — DEFAULT

GoToDefault: interpolation toward target pose  

---

### 2.7 — MOTION CONTROL MANAGER

Removal of other modes  
Keeping only oscillate  

---

### 2.8 — AUXILIARY METHODS

Nothing  

---

## 🚀 3. Procedure

1. Power on robot  
2. WiFi  
3. SSH LPC  
4. Compile controller  
5. ANYmal Software Launcher  
6. Lift then lower  
7. Suspend robot  
8. Manager:
   - reset  
   - manual play  
   - oscillator  

Version: 25.09  

---

## ⚠️ 4. Incident

Before (working deployment):

- no CSV  
- sinus  

Modification just before crash:

- CSV added  
- chirp  

Result:

- immediate trembling  
- no default  
- shutdown ~3s  

---

## ❗ 5. Abnormal points

- CSV should not impact since it only logs positions, but maybe writing the file in /tmp is not allowed by the LPC  
- chirp close to sinus because we limit to 2 Hz max  
- The robot started trembling strongly for 3 seconds and shut down immediately (battery cut), as if two controllers were running simultaneously  
